Application: Project Management Board
  Description: Track projects, sprints, and tasks from backlog to done
Id: 98883884-b402-42a0-858f-20defd9f1184

--- Identity ---

Users authenticate with stub
Scopes are "projects.view", "tasks.manage", "sprints.manage", and "projects.admin"

--- Roles ---

A "developer" has "projects.view" and "tasks.manage"
A "project manager" has "projects.view", "tasks.manage", "sprints.manage", and "projects.admin"
A "stakeholder" has "projects.view"

--- Content ---

Content called "projects":
  Each project has a name which is unique text, required
  Each project has a description which is text
  Each project has a status which is one of: "active", "on hold", "completed"
  Anyone with "projects.view" can view projects
  Anyone with "projects.admin" can create or update projects
  Anyone with "projects.admin" can delete projects

Content called "team members":
  Each team member has a name which is text, required
  Each team member has an email which is unique text, required
  Each team member has a role which is one of: "developer", "designer", "qa", "devops"
  Each team member has a project which references projects, required
  Anyone with "projects.view" can view team members
  Anyone with "projects.admin" can create or update team members

Content called "sprints":
  Each sprint has a name which is text, required
  Each sprint has a project which references projects, required
  Each sprint has a goal which is text
  Each sprint has a capacity which is a whole number, minimum 0
  Anyone with "projects.view" can view sprints
  Anyone with "sprints.manage" can create or update sprints

Content called "tasks":
  Each task has a title which is text, required
  Each task has a description which is text
  Each task has a project which references projects, required
  Each task has a sprint which references sprints
  Each task has an assignee which references team members
  Each task has a points which is a whole number, minimum 0
  Each task has a priority which is one of: "low", "medium", "high", "critical"
  Each task has a task lifecycle which is state:
    task lifecycle starts as backlog
    task lifecycle can also be in sprint, in progress, in review, or done
    backlog can become in sprint if the user has sprints.manage
    in sprint can become in progress if the user has tasks.manage
    in progress can become in review if the user has tasks.manage
    in review can become done if the user has tasks.manage
    in review can become in progress if the user has tasks.manage
    done can become in progress if the user has tasks.manage
  Anyone with "projects.view" can view tasks
  Anyone with "tasks.manage" can create or update tasks
  Anyone with "projects.admin" can delete tasks

Content called "time logs":
  Each time log has a task which references tasks, required
  Each time log has a team member which references team members, required
  Each time log has a hours which is currency
  Each time log has a logged at which is automatic
  Anyone with "projects.view" can view time logs
  Anyone with "tasks.manage" can create time logs

--- User Stories ---

As a developer, I want to see all tasks assigned to my sprint
  so that I know what to work on:
    Show a page called "Sprint Board"
    Display a table of tasks with columns: title, priority, task lifecycle, assignee, points
    Allow filtering by task lifecycle, priority, and sprint
    Allow searching by title
    This table subscribes to tasks changes

As a developer, I want to log time against a task
  so that we can track effort:
    Show a page called "Log Time"
    Accept input for task, team member, and hours

As a project manager, I want to create and manage tasks
  so that work is organized:
    Show a page called "Create Task"
    Accept input for title, description, project, sprint, assignee, points, and priority

As a project manager, I want to see project health metrics
  so that I can report progress to stakeholders:
    Show a page called "Project Dashboard"
    Display total task count with backlog vs done breakdown
    Display total time logged `sum(hours)`

As a project manager, I want to create new projects
  so that we can organize work:
    Show a page called "New Project"
    Accept input for name, description, and status

As a project manager, I want to plan sprints
  so that work is scheduled:
    Show a page called "Sprint Planning"
    Accept input for name, project, goal, and capacity

As a project manager, I want to manage the team
  so that people are assigned to projects:
    Show a page called "Team Management"
    Accept input for name, email, role, and project

--- Navigation ---

Navigation bar:
  "Board" links to "Sprint Board" visible to all
  "New Project" links to "New Project" visible to project manager
  "Create Task" links to "Create Task" visible to developer, project manager
  "Log Time" links to "Log Time" visible to developer
  "Sprint Planning" links to "Sprint Planning" visible to project manager
  "Team" links to "Team Management" visible to project manager
  "Dashboard" links to "Project Dashboard" visible to project manager, stakeholder

Stream task updates at /api/v1/stream
